<!-- Philosophy -->
<section id="philosophy">
  <h2>Philosophy</h2>
  <p>Most CSS frameworks ignore mobile-specific concerns, leaving you to bolt on safe areas, touch targets, and viewport fixes. VB takes the opposite approach: mobile support ships inside the core.</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Default</strong> &mdash; every page gets 44px touch targets on coarse pointers, <code>100dvh</code> body height, smooth scrolling, and responsive layout collapse. No attributes required.</li>
    <li><strong>Enhanced</strong> &mdash; pages designed for mobile add <code>viewport-fit=cover</code> to unlock safe-area tokens, use <code>data-page-layout="app-shell"</code> for bottom-nav shells, and use <code>&lt;dialog data-position="bottom"&gt;</code> for action sheets.</li>
    <li><strong>Granular</strong> &mdash; individual inputs get the right virtual keyboard via <code>inputmode</code>, <code>autocomplete</code>, and <code>enterkeyhint</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Because VB&rsquo;s design tokens drive all sizing and spacing, the <code>@media (pointer: coarse)</code> query only needs to set <code>--size-touch-min: 2.75rem</code> &mdash; every button, input, and select automatically adapts.</p>
</section>


<!-- Viewport Fit -->
<section id="viewport-fit">
  <h2>The viewport-fit Unlock</h2>
  <p>Modern phones have notches, Dynamic Islands, and home indicators that occupy real pixels. To respect these areas, add <code>viewport-fit=cover</code> to your viewport meta tag:</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Enable safe areas">{{ codeViewport | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>This activates VB&rsquo;s safe-area tokens, which are defined automatically in the token layer:</p>

  <code-block language="css" label="Safe-area tokens">{{ codeSafeArea | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>What auto-consumes safe areas</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Element</th>
        <th>Token used</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>dialog[data-position="bottom"]</code></td>
        <td><code>--safe-bottom</code> (padding)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-page-layout="app-shell"</code> nav (mobile)</td>
        <td><code>--safe-bottom</code> (padding)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>For custom fixed bars or sticky footers, apply safe-area tokens manually using <code>calc()</code>.</p>
</section>


<!-- What Works Already -->
<section id="already-works">
  <h2>What Works Already</h2>
  <p>These mobile features are built into VB&rsquo;s core &mdash; no extra attributes or configuration needed.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Concern</th>
        <th>VB solution</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Touch targets</td>
        <td><code>@media (pointer: coarse)</code> enforces 44px min on buttons, inputs, selects</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Full-height pages</td>
        <td><code>body { min-block-size: 100dvh }</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Tap highlight</td>
        <td><code>-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent</code> in reset</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>iOS text zoom</td>
        <td><code>text-size-adjust: none</code> in reset</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Smooth scrolling</td>
        <td><code>scroll-behavior: smooth</code> (respects reduced-motion)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Sidebar collapse</td>
        <td><code>data-layout="sidebar"</code> wraps naturally (intrinsic CSS, no media query)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Column &harr; row flip</td>
        <td><code>data-layout="switcher"</code> flips at configurable threshold</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Split stack</td>
        <td><code>data-layout="split"</code> stacks at &lt; 48rem</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Hover-only motion</td>
        <td><code>@media (hover: none)</code> disables hover lift/scale</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Scroll snap</td>
        <td>Built into <code>data-layout="reel"</code> and <code>&lt;carousel-wc&gt;</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Scroll containment</td>
        <td><code>overscroll-behavior: contain</code> on dialogs and sticky nav/aside</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>


<!-- App Shell -->
<section id="app-shell">
  <h2>App Shell Pattern</h2>
  <p>The <code>data-page-layout="app-shell"</code> layout creates a header/main/nav grid. On screens narrower than 48rem, the nav automatically moves below main &mdash; becoming a bottom navigation bar. Safe-area bottom padding is applied automatically.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="App shell layout">{{ codeAppShell | escape }}</code-block>

  <browser-window src="/docs/examples/demos/mobile-app-shell.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/mobile/app-shell" title="Mobile app shell demo" shadow></browser-window>

  <p>See also: <a href="/docs/patterns/application/shells/">Application Shells pattern</a></p>
</section>


<!-- Bottom Sheet -->
<section id="bottom-sheet">
  <h2>Bottom Sheet</h2>
  <p>VB&rsquo;s native <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code> styling includes a bottom drawer variant. It slides up from the bottom, has rounded top corners, respects safe areas, and prevents scroll chaining &mdash; all with zero JavaScript beyond the native <code>showModal()</code> API.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Bottom sheet with Invokers API">{{ codeBottomSheet | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>The <code>commandfor</code> / <code>command</code> attributes use the Invokers API to open and close the dialog declaratively. In browsers that don&rsquo;t support Invokers yet, fall back to <code>document.getElementById('my-sheet').showModal()</code>.</p>

  <browser-window src="/docs/examples/demos/mobile-bottom-sheet.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/mobile/bottom-sheet" title="Bottom sheet demo" shadow></browser-window>

  <p>See also: <a href="/docs/elements/native/dialog/">Dialog element docs</a></p>
</section>


<!-- Mobile Forms -->
<section id="forms">
  <h2>Mobile Forms</h2>
  <p>The single biggest mobile form improvement is using the right HTML attributes. These are native HTML &mdash; not VB features &mdash; but VB&rsquo;s <code>&lt;form-field&gt;</code> component makes them easy to use correctly.</p>

  <h3>The attributes that matter</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>What it does on mobile</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>type="email"</code></td>
        <td>Shows keyboard with <kbd>@</kbd> key prominent</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>type="tel"</code></td>
        <td>Shows numeric dialpad</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>inputmode="numeric"</code></td>
        <td>Numeric keyboard without spinners (use for credit cards, ZIP codes)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>autocomplete="email"</code></td>
        <td>Enables one-tap autofill from saved contacts</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>autocomplete="cc-number"</code></td>
        <td>iOS shows camera to scan physical card; Android offers Google Pay</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>autocomplete="one-time-code"</code></td>
        <td>iOS shows SMS suggestion bar above keyboard</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>enterkeyhint="next"</code></td>
        <td>Shows &ldquo;Next&rdquo; on the Enter key (guides user through the form)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>enterkeyhint="send"</code></td>
        <td>Shows &ldquo;Send&rdquo; on the last field</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <code-block language="html" label="Mobile-optimized form">{{ codeFormMobile | escape }}</code-block>

  <browser-window src="/docs/examples/demos/mobile-form.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/mobile/form" title="Mobile form demo" shadow></browser-window>

  <p>See also: <a href="/docs/attributes/autocomplete/">autocomplete reference</a>, <a href="/docs/attributes/inputmode/">inputmode reference</a>, <a href="/docs/attributes/enterkeyhint/">enterkeyhint reference</a></p>
</section>


<!-- Hero & Horizontal Scroll -->
<section id="hero-scroll">
  <h2>Hero and Horizontal Scroll</h2>

  <h3>Viewport height units</h3>
  <p>VB&rsquo;s cover layout supports three viewport height units:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Value</th>
        <th>Unit</th>
        <th>Use when</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-layout-min="100svh"</code></td>
        <td>Small viewport height</td>
        <td>Hero sections &mdash; always fits when browser chrome is visible</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-layout-min="100dvh"</code></td>
        <td>Dynamic viewport height</td>
        <td>Full-screen app panels &mdash; updates as chrome hides on scroll</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-layout-min="100vh"</code></td>
        <td>Legacy viewport height</td>
        <td>Fallback &mdash; broken on mobile (ignores browser chrome)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <code-block language="html" label="Hero with svh and dvh">{{ codeHero | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Horizontal card reel</h3>
  <p>The <code>data-layout="reel"</code> provides a horizontal scroll-snap container. It includes <code>scroll-snap-type: x mandatory</code>, momentum scrolling, and hidden scrollbars. Use it for card feeds, feature showcases, and image galleries.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Horizontal reel">{{ codeReel | escape }}</code-block>

  <browser-window src="/docs/examples/demos/mobile-hero.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/mobile/hero" title="Hero and reel demo" shadow></browser-window>
</section>


